Mets-Rockies Game at Denver’s Coors Field Postponed by Rain, Cold Weather

-- B y   L a r r y   S i d d o n s
-- 
2011-05-11T16:04:57Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-11/mets-rockies-game-at-denver-s-coors-field-postponed-by-rain-cold-weather.html
The  New York Mets ’ game against the
Colorado Rockies in Denver today has been postponed because of
rain and cold weather.  The game at Coors Field has been rescheduled for tomorrow,
the Rockies said in a news release. The starting time remains
1:10 p.m. Denver time.  The Denver area is expected to get more than two inches of
precipitation in the next 24 hours with wind chills in the upper
20s, according to Accuweather.com. The  Associated Press  said
parts of the Denver area may get snow from the storm.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Larry Siddons at 
 lsiddons@bloomberg.net  